The most obvious conclusion (https://www.imdb.com/title/tt10392366/reviews/?featured=rw7195322&ref_=tt_ururv_c_1_hd)
When I heard Toronto was holding the 2016 All-Star game that to me hinted that Toronto Raptors were going to be given the championship.
Raptors road to the championship began with the Derozan and Lowry era. At this time I stopped watching NBA but I was still aware of what was going on with the Raptors, They were a winning team due to agreed outcomes.
2018 rolled in, and the NBA did what they do best and sacrificed players so that Toronto can be given a championship so that it didn't seem obvious to the "fans". NBA swapped Derozen for Kawhi at this point it confirmed that the Raptors were going to be given the championship.
Then they got Gasol and other important pieces.
The Playoffs roll in, and it was the most obvious turn of events.
They lose the first game of the playoffs and they end up winning.
They lose first 2 in 2nd round then they catch up and win (just like the Bucks were allowed to beat the suns 2 year after.)
They have a slobberknocker battle vs Philly as a tribute to the Raptors' series vs Philly in 2001. The series ends the same exact way in 2019 just as it did in 2001. Is this a coincidence?
I question why Kawhi had to travel a radius of the court just to shoot the basketball. It's like they really wanted to resemble the 2001 ending of Raps vs Philly.
I also question the physics of the final shot of how the ball moved upon the rim. It looked as if they were using some sort of technology to ensure that the shot went in. Haha! Course they wouldn't do that, this is the NBA.
Then the finals rolled in.
GSW vs TR. Funny thing is Vince Carter was drafted by GSW and traded to the Raptors. Coincidentally, here we are TR vs GSW for the title. (Again, by this point I knew Toronto was going to be given the title).
Prior to that during the season Vince Carter reached 25000 point miles stone vs the Raptors by DUNKING on another player who wore the number 15. Is this a coincidence?
Anyways, The better team from what the NBA gave us was the GSW. They were the better team because of Durant and Magnet Boy. So what does the NBA do to give Toronto the championship? They create injuries for key players on GSW. Was this another coincidence?
So here we are in game 6, You know Toronto was known as the 6. We are in clutch mode. And Magnet Boy instead of dishing it to an open man for a quick bucket he decides to chuck the ball from 3 point coincidentally the magnets were turned off and the Raptors were given the title.
Remember Magnet Boy for some time was shooting from half court now during this series his shooting didn't exist.
Lastly, during the offseason, Kawhi decides to take his talents to the Lost Angels. To me, this looked like a favor for Kawhi and the NBA to play for the Raptors get a title, so he can get to play for his hometown as a reward. Maybe I am wrong?
Last Words: This was by far the most obvious season conclusion that I have ever seen. Remember, I knew Toronto were going to win in 2016. Maybe that's a coincidence too?
